docs.summary:
<!--ONLY:REST-->
Query Services using [WQL - Wix Query Language](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language) with [Cursor paging](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language#getting-started_api-query-language_cursor-paging) only.
Retrieves a list of services according to the provided filters and paging.

params.name: serviceId
params.doc: Id of the service to remove the staff member from.

docs.summary:
Removes a staff member from providing the service, applicable to service of type appointment only.
A staff members is a resource with tag "staff", the resource has to added as a provider to the service prior to removing it.

params.name: serviceId
params.doc: Id of the service to assign the custom slug to.

params.name: slugName
params.doc: The custom name to set as the active slug for the service.

docs.summary:
Sets a custom (user defined) slug to be used for the various service pages.
The call may fail in case there's another service with the same slug, either by past name, or by a custom set slug.

Update a Service, supports partial update
Pass the latest `revision` for a successful update

examples.title: UpdateService example
body: const result = await services.updateService(id, service, options);

params.name: slugName
params.doc: The custom name to validate as a slug for the service.

docs.summary:
Validate a custom (user defined) slug, making sure no other service uses the same slug.
The call may fail in case there's another service with the same slug, either by past name, or by a custom set slug.

members.name: sessionsDurations
members.doc:
A list of duration options for session times, in minutes. Minimum value for a duration is 1.
The availability calculation generates slots for sessions with these durations, where there is no conflict with existing sessions or other availability constraints.
Applicable and required for services of type appointment to allow the customer to book a session of the service.

members.name: timeBetweenSessions
members.doc:
The number of minutes between the `end` of one session, and the `start` of the next.
Minimum value is 0, maximum value is 720.

members.name: hasNext
members.doc:
Indicates if there are more results after the current page.
If `true`, another page of results can be retrieved.
If `false`, this is the last page.

members.name: rateType
members.doc:
The rate the Customer is expected to pay for the service.
Can be:
- Fixed - The service has a fixed price
- Custom - The service has a custom price, expressed as a price description.
- Varied - This service is offered with a set of different prices based on different terms.
- No Fee - This service is offered free of charge.

members.name: varied
members.doc:
The details of the varied pricing of the service
When **rateType** set to `VARIED` this field is required.

members.name: deposit
members.doc:
This service requires a deposit to be made online in order to book it.
When set to `true`, **rateType** must be set to `VARIED` or `FIXED`, and a `deposit` must be stated.

members.name: inPerson
members.doc: Customers can pay for the service in person.

members.name: online
members.doc:
Customers can pay for the service online.
When set to `true`, **rateType** must be set to `VARIED` or `FIXED`, and a `price` (or `defaultPrice`) must be stated.

members.name: pricingPlan
members.doc: Customers can pay for the service using a pricing plan.

members.doc:

When **rateType** set to `CUSTOM` this field is required.

When **rateType** set to `FIXED` this field is required.

members.name: varied
members.doc:
The details of the varied pricing of the service
When **rateType** set to `VARIED` this field is required.
